constituent: go, bushel basket, hamper, animal legs, eight, stone, rock
heisigStory: Bushel basket . . . stones. The key word refers to the Japanese game played with black and white colored stones on a lined board.
koohiiStory1: Go is chess played with stones.
koohiiStory2: The ignorant gaijin put a rook on top of his opponent´s stone when playing Go, much to the consternation of the Japanese players.
words:
碁盤(ごばん): Go board
碁(ご): go (board game)
